FBIS3-25716 "drafr039_a_94003" FBIS-AFR-94-039 Document Type:Daily Report 28 February 1994 CENTRAL AFRICA Cameroon Government Troops Sink Nigerian Boats in Clashes AB2702091094 London BBC World Service in English 0600 GMT 27 Feb 94 AB2702091094 London BBC World Service Language: English Article Type:BFN [From the "African News" program] [Text] State radio in Cameroon has given an account of fighting which took place early this month in the Bakassi Peninsula area which is disputed with Nigeria. It quoted a Cameroonian military official as saying 10 Nigerian boats, each carrying about 10 soldiers, had attacked a Cameroonian position. The radio said two of the boats were sunk and one Cameroonian soldier was killed and one wounded in the exchange nine days ago. A delegation from Cameroon has since held talks in Nigeria aimed at reducing tension.
